<div id="ctpl-mediumrectangle4" class="ctpl-mediumrectangle clearfix">
            <!-- hmb:go300 go300 ad -->
        <div id="GO300" class="galleryAd"></div>
    </div>
<!-- e hearst/ads/medium_rectangle_ad_gallery.tpl -->            </div>
                        <div class="gallery-overlay-outter lights-on hidden">
                <div class="gallery-overlay-inner">
                    <div class="gallery-overlay-title-container">
                        <div class="homeLink">
                            <span class="icon"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="gallery-overlay-title">ITV and startup announce Stamford hub, plan hundreds of jobs</div>
                        <div class="slide-count fade">
                            <div class="nav-stats"><span class="item-count-current">1</span><span>&nbsp;/&nbsp;</span><span class="item-count-total">5</span></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="thumbs-close-overlay hdn-analytics" data-hdn-analytics="gallery_thumbs_close|article-gallery-12943555|article-gallery-12943555|0">
                            <div class="thumbs-close-overlay-label"><span class="icon action"></span>Back to Gallery</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="gallery-close-overlay fade hdn-analytics" data-hdn-analytics="gallery_overlay_close|article-gallery-12943555|article-gallery-12943555|0">
                            <span class="icon action"></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
<!--/.hst-resgallery-container -->
<!-- e design/gallery/main_redesign.tpl -->                            </div><!-- /gallery float -->
                                <!-- fixed -->
                                                <div class="fixed-asset perfectPixel">
                        
            <!-- hearst/item/standalone.tpl -->
<div class="hdnce-e hdnce-item-43850"><!-- mid:freeform.43850 -->
<div id="hst-mediumrectangle4" class="hst-mediumrectangle">
	<div id="TMP300_3" class="ad_deferrable">
		
	</div>
</div>
</div><!-- / hdnce-e -->                            </div>
                        <!-- text -->
                        <p>Reality-show powerhouse ITV America will relocate a large portion of its operations to Stamford&rsquo;s South End and startup Wheelhouse Entertainment will set up in the same facility in a state-backed project expected to create about 450 jobs, officials announced Friday.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>The two companies would move into a vacant 90,000-square-foot building at 860 Canal St., where they would run operations including production, post-production and finance. The state is supporting the initiative with a $6 million loan to ITV America and a $3 million loan to Wheelhouse Entertainment. Partial loan forgiveness would be possible if certain job targets were met.</p>

            <!-- fixed -->
                                                <!-- fixed-asset perfectPixelWide -->
                        
            <!-- hearst/item/standalone.tpl -->
<div class="hdnce-e hdnce-item-47204"><!-- mid:freeform.47204 -->
<div class="fixed-asset perfectPixelWide ndn_embed" id="ndn-video-player-1" data-config-distributor-id="90010" data-config-width="100%" data-config-height="9/16w"></div>
</div><!-- / hdnce-e -->                            <!-- e fixed-asset perfectPixelWide -->
                        <!-- text -->
                        <p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a great sign when a company like ITV says it will consolidate a bunch of its operations in Connecticut,&rdquo; Catherine Smith, the state&rsquo;s economic development commissioner, said in an interview Friday. &ldquo;This is a good indicator that we have the right talent and location. We&rsquo;ve always felt digital media had a place in the state.&rdquo;</p>

            <!-- fixed -->
                                <div class="A300-placeholder collapse"></div>
            <!-- fixed -->
                                <!-- hearst/ads/duplicatable.tpl -->
<div class="ctpl-duplicated-ad">
              <!-- hmb:CONCERT1 CONCERT1 ad -->
         <div id="CONCERT1" class="ad_deferrable visible-xs" data-width="100%" data-height="100%">
            
        </div>
     </div>
<!-- / hearst/ads/duplicatable.tpl -->            <!-- text -->
                        <p>ITV and Wheelhouse could use the state funds to buy machinery and equipment and make capital improvements. In addition, both companies are eligible for film and digital media production and infrastructure tax incentives.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>&ldquo;As a leading creator of unscripted content, ITV America is focused on finding innovative ways to keep our business thriving while securing career opportunities for both current and future employees,&rdquo; ITV America CEO David George said in a statement. &ldquo;Our proposed partnership with the state of Connecticut delivers on both fronts. We&rsquo;re delighted to have worked with the governor&rsquo;s office on this plan, which allows us to service many of our current projects while also promoting growth at ITV America.&rdquo;</p>

            <!-- fixed -->
                                <div class="S300-placeholder collapse"></div>
            <!-- text -->
                        <p>ITV America describes itself as the largest independent non-scripted producer in the U.S. Its show portfolio includes &ldquo;Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen&rdquo; and &ldquo;The Four&rdquo; on Fox; &ldquo;Pawn Stars&rdquo; and &ldquo;Alone&rdquo; on History; &ldquo;Fixer Upper&rdquo; on HGTV; &ldquo;Real Housewives of New Jersey&rdquo; on Bravo; and &ldquo;Queer Eye&rdquo; on Netflix.</p>

            <!-- zone -->
                                            <div class="asset_zone zoneInlineD" data-config-asset-position="7">
                            <!-- src/business/widgets/hearst/collection/widget.tpl -->

    
<!-- noGen: collection_92a2b5cb9c6906035c2864fa225e1940_17360_ssl -->
<!-- e src/business/widgets/hearst/collection/widget.tpl -->                        </div>
                    <!-- text -->
                        <p>Wheelhouse&rsquo;s production arm, Spoke Studios, maintains a production partnership with ITV America, which also maintains offices in Manhattan and Los Angeles.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>&ldquo;The cornerstone of entrepreneurship is investing in people whose ideas and hard work create opportunity &mdash; precisely what drove Wheelhouse Entertainment to partner with ITV America and Gov. Malloy in this venture,&rdquo; Wheelhouse Entertainment CEO Brent Montgomery said in a statement. &ldquo;Building what we anticipate being one of the top production facilities on the East Coast is another way we aim to recruit and retain the first-class talent that ultimately produces the best programming.&rdquo;</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>City officials held a number of meetings with ITV to explain how moving to Stamford would support its operations, said Stamford Mayor David Martin. Ahead of the deal, 860 Canal was sold late last year for $7.6 million.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>&ldquo;This move reflects a team approach between the state and the city in helping to relocate and establish companies in Connecticut,&rdquo; Martin said in a statement. &ldquo;I am glad the state came through with the right incentive package, and my administration looks forward to helping ITV complete construction on the building and welcoming the new employees to Stamford as part of our expanding media family.&rdquo;</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>Connecticut is home to more than 1,200 media-related businesses that employ more than 16,000 people, according to state officials.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>Among media companies based in Stamford, NBC Sports Group and WWE are headquartered on the city&rsquo;s East Side.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>NBC Sports has its own incentives deal with the state, which supported the 2013 opening of its 300,000-square-foot complex at 1 Blachley Road. The agreement allotted up to some $26 million in loans.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>A number of production centers operate elsewhere in the city, including hubs at the Shippan Landing complex in the city&rsquo;s Shippan section, and on the West Side, near Stamford Hospital.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <p>ITV&rsquo;s and Wheelhouse&rsquo;s announcement follows professional-services firm PricewaterhouseCoopers&rsquo; announcement Thursday that it would add up to 450 jobs in the state and create a headquarters for its Insourced Solutions for Tax team at its existing downtown Stamford offices. Most of the new jobs would be based in Stamford. Up to $9 million in state grants would support PwC&rsquo;s expansion.</p>

            <!-- text -->
                        <em>
<p>pschott@scni.com; 203-964-2236; Twitter: @paulschott</p>
</em>

            
